parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds or navigating curves.
symptoms: The power steering suddenly stops working
the steering wheel shakes or jerks
the vehicle pulls to one side
the ESC (Electronic Stability Control) light comes on
the traction control light comes on
the power steering warning light comes on
and the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Power Steering Motor Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Power Steering Motor Control Module can cause loss of power steering, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The power steering warning light comes on
the traction control light comes on
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer
and the power steering system fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power reduction and engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
